Class SChoice

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Identifiable

    public class SChoice
extends AStruct
    A structural choice element can in principle be seen as a new root to a new parameter space definition, as it represents a choice for its parameter, possibly introducing multiple new sub-parameters. structural choices have to always be of their SPAram supertype, with the exception of Complex mappings, where the mapping can be chosen to be of another sub-type.
    Author:
    Felix Dobslaw
